===Final league table===
{{2014–15 Premier League table|showteam=SKE}}

==FA Cup==
{{Main|2014–15 FA Cup}}

Stoke were drawn at home against [[Conference Premier]] side [[Wrexham F.C.|Wrexham]] in the [[FA Cup]] third round. Stoke put in a disappointing display against the non-league side and fell behind after 73 minutes to a [[Mark Carrington (footballer)|Mark Carrington]] header. However Stoke avoided an embarrassing exit as a close range tap-in from [[Marko Arnautović]] and a brace from [[Stephen Ireland]] in the final ten minutes saw the Potters progress 3–1.<ref>{{cite web|title=Stoke v Wrexham|url=http://www.stokecityfc.com/fixtures-results/match-report/index.aspx?MatchId=3794853|website=Stoke City F.C|accessdate=4 January 2015}}</ref> In the fourth round Stoke came up against League One [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]] at [[Spotland Stadium|Spotland]]. Bojan volleyed Stoke into an early lead before he went off injured. From then on Rochdale had the better of the first half but were unable to beat [[Jack Butland]]. After half-time Stoke scored through [[Stephen Ireland]], [[Victor Moses]] and [[Jonathan Walters]] with [[Rhys Bennett]] getting a consolation for the Dale.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rochdale v Stoke|url=http://www.stokecityfc.com/fixtures-results/match-report/?matchid=3799242&tcmuri=2189117|website=Stoke City F.C|accessdate=27 January 2015}}</ref> Stoke faced Championship side [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]] in the fifth round and despite [[Peter Crouch]] scoring an early goal Stoke crashed to a 4–1 defeat.<ref>{{cite web|title=Blackburn 4-1 Stoke|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31423138|website=BBC Sport|accessdate=14 February 2015}}</ref>

