==League Cup==
{{Main|2014–15 Football League Cup}}

Stoke were drawn at home to [[Football League Two|League Two]] side [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] in the second round of the League Cup. The Potters were able to claim a 3–0 victory with a brace from [[Jonathan Walters]] and a strike from [[Peter Crouch]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Stoke City 3, Portsmouth 0: Potters head for Sunderland after crushing Capital Cup triumph|url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Stoke-City-3-Portsmouth-0-Potters-head-Sunderland/story-22837670-detail/story.html|website=Stoke Sentinel|accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Stoke City 3, Portsmouth 0: SJW inspires a capital show by Potters|url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Stoke-City-3-Portsmouth-0-SJW-inspires-capital/story-22837661-detail/story.html|website=Stoke Sentinel|accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref> It was a comfortable victory for Stoke and manager [[Mark Hughes]] was able to give a professional debut to academy player [[Ollie Shenton]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Future Is Bright|url=http://www.stokecityfc.com/news/article/the-future-is-bright-1883348.aspx|website=Stoke City F.C|accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref> Stoke faced fellow Premier League side Sunderland in the fourth round and despite falling behind to a [[Jozy Altidore]] strike, two goals from [[Marc Muniesa]] earned Stoke their first ever win at the [[Stadium of Light]] and progression to the next round.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sunderland 1, Stoke City 2: Full-time match report|url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Sunderland-1-Stoke-City-2-time-match-report/story-22969415-detail/story.html|website=Stoke Sentinel|accessdate=24 September 2014}}</ref> In the Fourth Round Stoke faced Southampton and after an abject first half display found themselves 2–0 down. Stoke improved in the second half and goals from [[Steven Nzonzi]] and [[Mame Biram Diouf]] brought it back level before Peter Crouch was then sent-off for two bookable offences and the Saints went and scored the decisive third goal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Martin Spinks' match report from the Capital One Cup tie  |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Stoke-City-2-Southampton-3-Martin-Spinks-match/story-23755373-detail/story.html|website=Stoke Sentinel|accessdate=30 October 2014}}</ref>

